Job Description

Why join us?
In order to address its upcoming challenges, BlaBlaCar is migrating its Backend Architecture to a Service Oriented one. Within the Inventory team, you will have the opportunity to scale BlaBlaCar’s core business and help us become the number #1 destination for road transport.
By joining our experimented and talented engineering team, you will contribute to design and develop a new service dedicated to the very core of BlaBlaCar: trip publication and booking; making sure it is robust and scalable.
The core of our stack is composed of Java, Kafka, MariaDB, PHP/Symfony (legacy).
Thanks to your technical expertise and communication skills you will work closely with our front-end squads and product experts.

What you will directly contribute to:
Reporting to the Engineering Manager, in a team of 3 engineers (to date);
Building a robust and scalable backend service that support BlaBlaCar websites and mobile apps;
Working on a CQRS and Event Sourcing architecture;
Taking part in the design definition of the services and their APIs to ensure they are scalable, robust and easy to use;
Interacting with multiple internal stakeholders (front-end developers, product managers, business analysts, data scientists, etc.);
Deploying and operating your services to production and ensuring they are performing as expected through monitoring and instrumentation;
Helping us improving our agile team processes (Scrum methodology) and animating some of our team rituals.

Qualifications

What you will need to be successful:
Master JAVA (Spring Framework) and eager to constantly learn new technologies;
A minimum of 4 years of experience in engineering teams within hyper-growth tech companies;
A strong ability to lead analysis based on product specifications and needs;
Practical knowledge of ops tools (monitoring, deployment, containers, linux…) and
willingness to contribute to building a true DevOps environment;
Experience in Service Oriented Architecture ecosystem, as well as technologies such as Kafka;
PHP/Symfony, Docker, is a plus
A first experience in Event-Driven Architecture (EDA) is a strong plus;
Product-oriented spirit with the ambition to deliver the best experience to end-users;
Be humble, structured, organized, motivated by innovation and a relentless doer;
Enjoy working as a team-player and learning from others;
Fluent in spoken and written English; proficiency in French is a plus.

Additional Information

A few practical details about the role:
Start: As soon as you are ready!
Location: Paris
Contract: Long-term contract
Compensation: Competitive package based on experience

What we offer all of our employees:
The opportunity to have a meaningful impact, building a CO2-saving global travel network enabling strong human connections too.
A strong “Fun & Serious” company culture
An international environment with a team counting 35 nationalities, serving a global member-base from 8 offices around the world (Berlin, Kiev, Madrid, Milan, Moscow, Paris (HQ), São Paulo, Warsaw)
State-of-the-art office spaces, in a great location
And some other great perks!

Free carpooling to live our value “Be The Member”.
Annual BlaBlaBreak which takes us all for an unforgettable weekend
Possibility to work from another BlaBlaOffice abroad for a week once a year (BlaBlaSwap)
The choice between the latest Mac or PC equipment
Opportunity to attend Tech conferences in France and Europe
A start-up spirit grounded in agility & teamwork
Challenging career opportunities in a high-growth and fast-paced environment
Bi-Weekly team-all BlaBlaTalks to learn from each other
Weekly Tech Demos, so that we’re all up to date with where our product stands

A few practical details about the role:
Start: As soon as you are ready!
Location: Paris HQ
Contract: Permanent contract
Compensation: Competitive package based on experience

What we offer all of our employees:
A start-up spirit that fosters agility, teamwork and impact;
Challenging career opportunities in a high-growth and fast-paced environment;
An inspiring working environment including state-of-the-art office spaces;
Free carpooling to live our value “Be The Member”;
Annual BlaBlaBreak which takes us all for an unforgettable weekend;
Possibility to do a BlaBlaSwap once a year and go work from another BlaBlaOffice abroad;
Bi-Weekly BlaBlaTalks when we learn from each other
Weekly Tech Demos
The choice between the latest Mac or PC equipment (for Tech only)
Opportunity to attend Tech conferences in France and Europe (for Tech only)

What is next?
If you are ready to join our exciting journey, please apply below: upload your resume in English (PDF format) and answer our questions in English.
Kindly note that only complete applications will be reviewed by our hiring team and that all your information will be kept confidential.
You can expect us to review your application within the following 3 weeks. If your application and profile fit our requirements, we will invite you for an HR and technical phone interview, a first technical exercise through our visio conference tool and 1 onsite interview.
BlaBlaCar is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.

Bachelor’s or Master's degree in Finance, Accounting, Business, Engineering or a related discipline;
Basic SQL knowledge
Proven expertise in finance management, evaluation, and swift analysis: you always deliver meaningful business support;
Proven ability as a manager of strategic relationships with business partners: you are able to take and/or influence decisions;
Demonstrated analytical, financial acumen in delivering forecasting, budgeting and variance analysis, as well as data interpretation of business impact and results;
Advanced proficiency in MS Excel (e.g. using pivots, lookups, and so on);
Ability to travel; 15%+ travel expected;

Are you an Amazonian?

Come build the future with us! What unites all Amazonians (across teams and geographies) is that we are striving to delight our customers and make their lives easier—whoever they may be. In pursuit of delighting customers, Amazonians have developed many products and services that have transformed the way our customers live their lives and run their businesses. Together we are building the future, one innovative product, service, and idea at a time. Wherever you are in the business – whatever team, whatever level - we all work to one set of Leadership Principles that help us hire the right people and run our business in the best way. These principles are followed every single day. They are highlighted in the way we interact with each other and how we behave. They are: Customer Obsession; Ownership; Invent and Simplify; Are Right, A Lot; Learn and Be Curious; Hire and Develop the Best; Insist on the Highest Standards; Think Big; Bias for Action, Frugality; Earn Trust; Dive Deep; Have Backbone – Disagree and Commit; and Deliver Results.

About Amazon Operations

Amazon Operations sits at the heart of the Amazon customer experience. We deal with the ‘everyday experience’ of shopping on Amazon. We look after everything from the moment a customer click’s buy, to the moment that item gets delivered – from desktop to doorstep. Across Europe we have more than 50 fulfilment centres, hundreds of delivery stations, thousands of machines, and tens of thousands of employees, all working together in harmony to make sure the right item gets delivered to the right person in the right place at the right time.
At Amazon we're working to be the most customer-centric company on earth. To get there, we need exceptionally talented, bright, and driven people. Amazon is one of the most recognizable brand names in the world and we distribute millions of products each year to our loyal customers.

We are looking for a talented EU Cost Control & Reporting Manager to help manage our ever-growing cost control & reporting needs and support analysis of an increasingly complex business related to high volume hiring (HVH) across the EU.

You will be responsible for designing, executing, maintaining and improving our reporting portfolio and cost controlling. You will work closely with a wide range of business professionals across Amazon to leverage our data in ways that provide business insights.

Your data driven mindset as Senior Business Analyst will enable you to be a key contributor in our efforts to enhance and drive our cost strategy in the area of High Volume Hiring.

But you won’t stop there. Your role is also responsible for turning marketing campaign data and results into actionable and insightful information, by developing, executing standardized reporting, and analysis that will provide clear insights on customer behavior and marketing activities impact on High Volume Hiring.

Main Responsibilities:
Managing and participating in cross-functional business activities across several geographies in EU;
Constantly challenging the status quo and proposing alternative solutions to drive the efficiency;
Establish scalable, efficient, automated processes for data analyses and cost controlling
Implementing policies and programs that guide Workforce staffing towards maintaining and improving its competitive position and profitability;
Partner with your team, by managing all weekly and monthly financial activities related to workforce staffing, including forecasting, planning and reporting
Working with data source providers and technology teams, ensuring that key decision data is accurate, automated and timely.
Develop and Implement Marketing Controlling process for workforce staffing

Advanced problem solving and root cause analysis ability, combined with confident communication skills for conveying your conclusions;
You’re highly analytical, detail-oriented and bring a strong sense of business acumen: you have a track record of managing new ideas and creative solutions;
You can manage and prioritize your workload in a fast-paced, high-growth, occasionally ambiguous environment;
You have experience of working with large-scale data mining and reporting tools;
Previous experience as a manager in a Manufacturing, Distribution Centre or Logistics environment;
MBA and/or Professional certification (CPA/CMA etc.);

ManoMano’s priority is to deliver excellent Customer Experience and aim to become a leader in this area. To reach our objective, we seek to deliver an irreproachable service, particularly thanks to an innovative and optimized Customer and Seller Support.
Inside the Customer Service & Seller Support Operations team, the Voice of the Customer Programme is transversal to the organisation, tackling issues and driving change for different teams from Customer Service and Seller Support to Presales advice. Our role is to improve the user experience through resolution process and continuous improvement based heavily on data.
Our Customer Insights Data Analyst will work hand in hand with almost every team in the company, not acting as support but bringing actionable recommendations. If you love managing cross-functional stakeholders, pushing projects forward to deliver measurable and strategically meaningful results, and solving problems from both a mile high as well as deep down in the details, this is the role for you !
Your job will have a considerable impact on ManoMano’s growth
Your main tasks will include:
Definition and optimisation of key performance indicators;
Tools and reporting creationConsolidation, optimisation and automation of resolution processes;
Advanced analytics on Customer and Seller experience;
Transversal projects (Product, Data, Outsourcing…).
Preferred Experience
Business and / or analytics background, bac + 5 or equivalent;
4-5 years experience in an analytical position (Consultant, Analyst…);
A passion for data analysis, data visualisation & optimisation;
Customer-centricity;
A strong analytical & detail-oriented mindset;
Full autonomy in problem solving;
The ability to synthesise and explain analyses;
A creative mindset to identify solutions & shortcuts;
The capacity to design automated tools;
Mastering SQL;
E-Commerce experience is a plus !
WHAT MANOMANO HAS TO OFFER :
An exciting challenge that involves scaling up to become the next French unicorn;
An immersion in the world of e-commerce and on-line marketplaces;
An Agile & International Environment (France, Italy, Spain, the United Kingdom, Germany) with brilliant and friendly colleagues;
The ability to work from home one day a week;
A pleasant working environment in the heart of Paris;
7 weeks of paid holidays per year, meal vouchers card, health insurance, transportation;
Work-life balance.
Additional Information
Contract Type: Full-Time
Start Date: 02 September 2019
Location: Paris, France (75017)
Education Level: Master's Degree
Experience: > 1 year
Telecommuting Possible

Dans le cadre d’une création de poste au sein de l’équipe marketing de Homebrella, en direct avec la responsable marketing, vous mettez votre expérience et vos idées au service de la construction d’une stratégie d’acquisition structurée et ambitieuse pour notre marque.

Celle-ci s’articulera sur les leviers digitaux (PPC, RTB, retargeting, social, etc.), mais pas que. Grâce à votre esprit innovant et votre flair pour déceler les opportunités :

vous identifierez des relais de croissance à tester (partenariats, plateformes d’apporteurs d’affaires…);
vous concevrez des opérations de promotion produit;
vous mettrez en place des campagnes de communication sur des cibles spécifiques qui nous permettront de faire croître notre portefeuille de clients;
vous explorerez ces pistes avec créativité et méthode.
Plus particulièrement :
vous fixerez les KPIs qui vous permettront de valider ou d’infirmer vos hypothèses de tests;
vous construirez et suivrez assidûment des tableaux de bord pour prendre vos décisions et pour informer le top management;
vous coordonnerez et emmènerez avec vous les équipes en interne et les partenaires externes;
vous ne manquez pas d’idées à mettre en place pour atteindre les objectifs qu’on vous fixe et vous êtes armé(e)s d’une volonté de fer pour faire grandir les projets en lesquels vous croyez.
On vous promet que vous n’allez pas vous ennuyer !

Profil recherché Votre profil :
vous justifiez d’une expérience de 1 an minimum en agence ou chez l’annonceur sur des missions similaires;
vous maîtrisiez les canaux d’acquisition classiques et leurs subtilités (Google Ads, Bing Ads, Display, Retargeting, Social Ads, etc...);
les chiffres et l’analyse, c’est votre dada !
vous avez une approche ROIste;
vous aimez les responsabilités, vous savez sortir de votre champ de compétences, vous aimez l’idée de tester et d’apprendre...
Bref, vous avez super envie de participer à plein de nouvelles choses dans un environnement startup.

Vos qualités :
vous êtes curieux et force de proposition, vous aimez vous challenger vous-même;
vous êtes proactif et avez le sens du travail en équipe;
vous faites preuve d’une grande rigueur dans l’exécution de vos missions et d’une organisation sans faille;
vous êtes réfléchi et fin(e) analyste : les chiffres vous servent à prendre vos décisions;
vous êtes pragmatique et bon communicant.
Vos avantages :
Tickets Restaurant;
Remboursement de 50% pass Navigo;
Mutuelle d’entreprise + Prévoyance + surcomplémentaire retraite;
Intéressement et plan d’actions salariés;
Un cadre de travail dynamique et challengeant;
Des projets digitaux innovants;
Des opportunités d’évolution en interne ou au sein du groupe Admiral (Espagne, Italie, Grande-Bretagne, etc.).
Entreprise L’olivier est un assureur en ligne en très forte croissance. Nous avons pour ambition de devenir le leader de l'assurance en France !

En rejoignant L’olivier, vous aurez l’opportunité de contribuer à des projets innovants portés par une forte culture du test & learn et une approche data-driven. Et ce n’est pas tout : chaque collaborateur, animé d'une envie d'améliorer nos pratiques, peut exprimer son idée et prendre le lead sur sa concrétisation.

Intégrer L’olivier, c’est également bénéficier de la solidité financière du groupe Admiral, leader européen de l’assurance en ligne, coté à la Bourse de Londres. Aujourd’hui, plus de 6 millions de clients font confiance à Admiral dans le monde.

L’olive sur le gâteau : nous sommes une entreprise proche de nos collaborateurs. Et oui, nous recevons chaque année, depuis 2015 déjà, le label Great Place To Work.

L'olivier assurance a lancé en janvier 2019, Homebrella, une assurance habitation à destination des locataires. Homebrella a de fortes ambitions de croissance et entend dépoussiérer l’assurance des locataires en leur facilitant la vie : parcours tout digital, sans engagement et 100% bilingue pour les expatriés !

Pourquoi nous rejoindre ?

Des opportunités d’évolution en interne, ou au sein du groupe Admiral (Espagne, Italie, Grande-Bretagne, etc...) ;

Un cadre de travail dynamique et challengeant ;

Des projets digitaux innovants ;

Des collègues motivés et sympathiques.

Job Description

Le poste est à pourvoir en CDI dans la DSI du Siège International d’Ubisoft à Paris, et plus particulièrement au sein de l’équipe « EBS » dont le rôle est de créer les meilleurs outils pour les employés d’Ubisoft.
Vous travailleriez en binôme avec un autre développeur (qui a un profil plutôt backend) sur des projets de création d’applications et de services web en lien avec la Data.
Concrètement, vous seriez en relation avec une équipe de Data Scientists et de Data Analysts qui ont des besoins en termes d’outils ou d’applications maison : Ils fournissent l’algorithme, vous fournissez le design, l’UX et le développement de l’application.
L’objectif est de créer des outils les plus efficaces possibles pour permettre à nos spécialistes Data de réaliser des analyses poussées et des recommandations prédictives.
À ce titre, vos missions seront les suivantes :
Échanger avec les équipes Data afin de comprendre, cadrer leurs besoins et leur proposer les solutions techniques les plus adaptées ;
Créer et développer la partie Front-end des applications en partenariat avec votre binôme en charge du Back-End ;
Être garant de la performance et de la scalabilité du code Front-End ;
Participer aux décisions concernant les features et l’architecture Front-end des applications ;
Être le référent Front-End des différentes équipes impliquées dans le projet.

Qualifications

Background
Diplôme supérieur en informatique ou équivalent ;
Expérience minimum de 4 ans en tant que développeur Front-End.
Compétences requises
Excellente maîtrise du triptyque JavaScript / HTML5 / CSS3 ;
Connaissance approfondie d’Angular (6+) ;
Être capable de travailler au sein d’une équipe agile ;
Volonté de réaliser des interfaces “pixel perfect“ ;
Anglais courant.
Compétences bonus
Connaissance d’une ou plusieurs bibliothèques JS (Bootstrap, Kendo UI components, Ngx-Charts…) ;
Expérience du TDD et/ou connaissance des frameworks de test Mocha et Jasmine ;
Intérêt pour les jeux vidéo.

Additional Information

